<TITLE> AL more keen on keeping pledges to foreign state: BNP </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 5 (bdnews24.com)The ruling Awami League is fulfilling its pledges to foreign states instead of election pledges to people, a senior BNP leader said. "[So] the people are upset," Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain told a discussion to mark late president Ziaur Rahman's 28th death anniversary in National Press Club on Friday. He accused the government of 'selling out' the country's sovereignty and independence by allowing India to construct Tipaimukh Dam and giving it corridor by joining the proposed Asian Highway. He called on the people to resist the move. Mosharraf, a former water resources minister in the Khaleda administration, said the cabinet ministers are saying what the Indian ministers are saying. He repeated views held by both the government and the opposition that the BDR mutiny aimed to weaken the border force and the army. The probes made by the government and the army seem to be conflicting. It went to show that the government probe was not neutral. BNP"s associate organisation Doctors Association of Bangladesh hosted the meeting chaired by its president AKM Azizul Haque
